Key features for the dataset might include:

Temperature (°C): The average temperature of the region over a given period.

Precipitation (mm): The monthly or yearly rainfall or snow accumulation data.

Glacier Mass Balance (kg/m²): A measure of the glacier's accumulation and ablation.

Snowfall (mm): Monthly or yearly snowfall in the region.

Elevation (meters): Elevation of the glacier or surrounding area.

Season (Season type): Whether it's winter or summer (as it affects the melting rate).

Solar Radiation (W/m²): Amount of solar radiation received by the glacier.

Glacier Area (km²): The surface area of the glacier.

Glacier Thickness (meters): How thick the glacier is at various locations.

Date: Temporal feature indicating when the data was recorded.
